(8, 1, '"Directions: Read each situation and choose the BEST alternative.\r\nSituation: Pete has a financial problem and Mr. Thompson has approved a loan for him. Pete says:"\r\n', 'How nice of you to approve it!', 'I really appreciate your help.', 'What a kind man you are!', 'I think you’re a generous man. Thanks.', 'I really appreciate your help.\r\n', 'เนื่องจาก Pete มีปัญหา โดย Mr. Thompson ได้ให้ความช่วยเหลือ Pete จึงต้องพูดขอบคุณ\r\n'),
(8, 2, '"Directions: Read each situation and choose the BEST alternative.\r\nSituation: Lisa is visiting a sick colleague at the hospital. She says:"\r\n', 'Don’t worry. Make yourself at home.', 'Take it easy. Time flies.', 'Calm down. Take a rest for a while.', 'Get well soon. We miss you at the office.', 'Get well soon. We miss you at the office.\r\n', 'sick colleague แปลว่าเพื่อนร่วมงานที่ป่วย คำตอบที่ถูกต้องจึงต้องมี at the office.\r\n'),
(8, 3, '"Directions: Read each situation and choose the BEST alternative.\r\nSituation: Mrs. Green asks her daughter what her new roommate at the university dormitory is like. Her daughter says:"\r\n', 'She’s tall and slim.', 'She’s got long dark hair.', 'She’s friendly and cheerful.', 'She likes swimming and skiing.\r\n', 'She’s friendly and cheerful.', 'โจทย์ถามว่า what her new rommate at the university dormitory is like.ซึ่ง is like มีความหมายว่า มีลักษณะนิสัยอย่างไร\r\n'),
(8, 4, '"Directions: Read each situation and choose the BEST alternative.\r\nSituation: After dinner, Anna asks her friend if he enjoyed the food she prepared. Her friend says:"\r\n', 'It was wonderful. You’re a great cook.', 'Well, it looked good. But I’m on diet.', 'That’s well done. I do have a great time.', 'It appears delicious. I should be invited again.', 'It was wonderful. You’re a great cook.', 'คำตอบ It was wonderful. You’re a great cook.. เป็นคำตอบที่เหมาะสมที่สุดไม่โอเวอร์จนเกินไป ไม่แย่จนเกินไป\r\n'),
(8, 5, '"Directions: Read each situation and choose the BEST alternative.\r\nSituation: Kari invites Jenny to go to a concert. Jenny has to finish an assignment, so she says:"\r\n', 'I like that idea. I’ll make a decision.', 'That’s marvelous. I don’t want to go.', 'That’s fine. But sorry, it’s not possible for we.\r\n.', 'That sounds great. But I don’t think I can make it.', 'That sounds great. But I don’t think I can make it.\r\n', 'เนื่องจาก Jenny ยังทำงานของตัวเองไม่เสร็จ จึงคิดว่าไม่น่าจะไปด้วยได้ ดังนั้นควรตอบThat sounds great. But I don’t think I can make it.\r\n'),
(8, 6, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe boy claimed that the pencil box belonged to him, but soon everybody found out that he___."\r\n', 'is lying', 'tells a lie', 'has told a lie', 'had told a lie.', 'has told a lie', 'เนื่องจากรูปประโยคทั้งหมด อยู่.ใน tense Past perfect con. จึงต้องตอบเป็น Past perfect con.\r\n'),
(8, 7, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe little girl held her mother’s hand firmly ____ the other side of the street."\r\n', 'if they walk along', 'until they walked to', 'when they walk down', 'as they walked over', 'until they walked to\r\n', 'คำตอบ until they walked to เป็นคำตอบที่เข้ากับรูปประโยค\r\n'),
(8, 8, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nWhy didn’t you give something to the taxi driver ____?"\r\n', 'who has brought your briefcase to you', 'whom your briefcase you brought to\r\n', 'who brought you your briefcase', 'that to you he brought your briefcase\r\n', 'who brought you your briefcase', 'who brought you your briefcase เป็นประโยคที่ถูกต้อง ที่แปลว่า คนที่เป็นคนเจอกระเป๋าของคุณ\r\n'),
(8, 9, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe Boy Scouts had to take ____ to the camp, each carrying a heavy backpack."\r\n', 'a two-mile hike', 'a two miles hike', 'a two-miles’ hike', 'a hike in two miles', 'a two-mile hike', 'a two-mile hike ถูกต้องตามหลักแกรมม่า\r\n'),
(8, 10, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nIt is required that the new Japanese student ____ in an extra English conversation course."\r\n', 'enroll', 'enrolled', 'will enroll', 'would enroll', 'enroll', 'enroll ถูกต้องตามหลักแกรมม่า'),
(8, 11, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe customer wanted to know ___."\r\n', 'she could find a can of baked beans where', 'where could she find a can of baked beans\r\n', 'a can of baked beans was where she could find', 'where she could find a can of baked beans\r\n', 'where she could find a can of baked beans', 'where ต้องคนต้นประโยค ตามด้วย ประธาน(she) ตามด้วย verb ( could find)'),
(8, 12, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe author wishes that _____ in an international journal the year before."\r\n', 'he publishes his article', 'he published his article', 'his article will be published\r\n', 'his article had been published', 'his article had been published', 'the year before. เป็นตัวบอกว่า เกิดขึ้นเมื่อปีก่อน ดังนั้นต้องใช้ Past perfect tense ในการตอบ'),
(8, 13, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nEach kind of pet should be fed and ____ according to its individual requirements."\r\n', 'treat.', 'treated.', 'is to treat.', 'has treated.', 'treated.', 'should be fed fed เป็นช่องสอง ดังนั้นต้องตอบเป็น V.2 ของ treat ด้วย'),
(8, 14, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nDr. Jackson, ____, displayed his scientific genius when he was still a boy of five."', 'university’s prominent scientist', 'universities’ prominent scientist', 'the prominent scientist of university', 'a prominent scientist of the university', 'a prominent scientist of the university', 'prominent scientist เป็นชื่อตำแหน่งต้องนำหน้าด้วย a'),
(8, 15, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nAnybody who wants to lose weight must avoid diets ____ carbohydrates."\r\n', 'which contains', 'that contain', 'which contained', 'that are containing', 'that contain', 'จากรูปประโยค diets มีอยู่ใน carbohydrates ดังนั้นต้องใช้ that ที่เป็นตัวเชื่อม'),
(8, 16, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nThe guide reminded the tourists what to take along with them, what to wear and ____."\r\n', 'where to meet the next morning', 'the next morning where to be met', 'where they will meet the next morning', 'where should they meet the next morning', 'where to meet the next morning\r\n', 'จากประโยคข้างหน้า what to wear ต้องตามด้วย where to meet'),
(8, 17, '"Directions: Read each sentence and choose the alternative that BEST completes it.\r\nI understand that ____ earlier, but I could not find your address."\r\n', 'I have sent you the letter', 'I might sent you the letter to you', 'the letter will be sent to you', 'I should have sent you the letter', 'I should have sent you the letter\r\n', 'ประโยคหลังเป็น could ประโยคหน้าต้องใช้ should'),
