(9, 1, '"Student: What do I have to do if I want to withdraw from course?\r\nTeacher: If you want to _______ the course, you have to go to the college office."\r\n', 'do', 'drop', 'take', 'attend', 'drop', 'การ withdraw หรือถอนในมหาวิทยาลัยใช้คำว่า drop'),
(9, 2, '"Tom: Are you going to phone Patricia again?\r\nPeter: _________ I’ve left five messages for her, and she’s never replied."\r\n', 'I haven’t', 'I’d bothered.', 'She doesn’t want to.', 'I can’t be bothered.', 'I can’t be bothered.', 'I can’t be bothered. แปลว่าฉันไม่สามารถรบกวนเขาได้อีก ซึ่งตรงกับรูปประโยค'),
(9, 3, '"William: Can you come round for a meal tonight?\r\nPat: Thanks very much. _______ I haven’t met you for a long time."\r\n', 'I doubt it.', 'I’d love to.', 'SI wish I were.', 'That looks good.\r\n', 'I’d love to.', '\'I\'d love to. แปลว่าอยากทำเช่นนั้นเช่นกันซึ่งมักตามหลังประโยค Thank very much\''),
(9, 4, '"James: What did you think of your brother’s new girlfriend?\r\nJane: _________ I got on with her very well."\r\n', 'She’s fantastic.', 'She looks awful.', 'She’s lost weight.', 'She’s in her thirties.', 'She’s fantastic.', 'Jane ตอบว่า I got on with her very well แสดงว่าไปด้วยกันได้ดี'),
(9, 5, '"Kevin: Hi, Manee (?)________\r\nManee: Hi, I’m great. I’m going to visit my uncle in Songkhla.\r\nAnnouncement: “Ladies & Gentlemen. Attention please! Train 2637, Hualumpong Express, bound for Hadyai will leave at 21.30 hours form platform 3.”\r\nManee: I’m sorry, Kevin. _______ I’ll see you later. There is an announcement about your train also. Bye!"\r\n', 'How’s it like?', 'How about you?', 'How do you do?.', 'How have you been?', 'How have you been?', 'ประโยคที่ใช้ทักทายถามว่าเป็นยังไงบ้างใช้ How have you been?'),
(9, 6, '"Kevin: Hi, Manee ________\r\nManee: Hi, I’m great. I’m going to visit my uncle in Songkhla.\r\nAnnouncement: “Ladies & Gentlemen. Attention please! Train 2637, Hualumpong Express, bound for Hadyai will leave at 21.30 hours form platform 3.”\r\nManee: I’m sorry, Kevin. (?)_______ I’ll see you later. There is an announcement about your train also. Bye!"\r\n', 'Keep your time.', 'Someone is calling me.', 'You can wait for me here.', 'My train is about to leave.\r\n', 'My train is about to leave.', 'เนื่องจากมีเสียงประกาศจากสถานนีว่ามีรถจะออกซึ่งน่าจะเป็นรถไฟของ Manee ดังนั้นจึงต้องตอบว่า My train is about to leave'),
(9, 7, '"Situation: George walks into a furniture store. He only wants to browse.\r\nShop assistant: ___(?)___, sir?\r\nGeorge: No, thanks. ______.\r\nShop assistant: All right. If you need any help, just let me know."\r\n', 'Can I help you', 'Do you want to look around', 'Would you like to buy something', 'Would you mind helping me\r\n', 'Can I help you', 'Can I help you เป็นประโยคคำถามที่นิยมใช้เวลาถามคนที่ต้องการความช่วยเหลือ'),
(9, 8, '"Situation: George walks into a furniture store. He only wants to browse.\r\nShop assistant: ______, sir?\r\nGeorge: No, thanks. ___(?)___.\r\nShop assistant: All right. If you need any help, just let me know."\r\n', 'I don’t need any help', 'It’s my pleasure', 'I’m just looking', 'There’s no need to bother you', 'I’m just looking', '\'George ตอบเป็น No,thanks แสดงว่ายังไม่ต้องารความช่วยเหลือซึ่งควรตอบแบบเหมาะสามคือ I\'m just looking\''),
(9, 9, '"Situation: Jane is trying to calm down her friend, Judy.\r\nJane: Why are you crying, Judy? ___(?)___\r\nJudy: My little kitten, she died last night.\r\nJane: ______"\r\n', 'How have you been?', 'How’s everything?', 'What’s the matter?', 'How sad are you?\r\n', 'What’s the matter?', 'What’s the matter? เป็นประโยคที่ใช้ถามไถ่ความเป็นไปในกรณีที่อยากให้ผู้ตอบเล่าให้ฟัง'),
(9, 10, '"Situation: Jane is trying to calm down her friend, Judy.\r\nJane: Why are you crying, Judy? ______\r\nJudy: My little kitten, she died last night.\r\nJane: ___(?)___"\r\n', 'It doesn’t matter.', 'I’m sorry to hear that.', 'How sad you are!\r\n', 'I wish she wouldn’t die.', 'I’m sorry to hear that.', 'เนื่องจาก ลูกแมวของ Judy ตายจึงควรแสดงความเสียใจจากเรื่องที่ได้ยิน'),
(9, 11, 'Situation: Sandy is hungry. She wants to eat some cookies she bought last night, but she finds that all the cookies are gone.\r\nSandy: Jim, where are the cookies? Don\'t tell me you ate them all! Again!\r\nJim: Yes, I did. ___(?)___. They were so good.\r\nSandy: I thought you didn\'t like cookies.\r\nJim: Well, I don\'t like cookies flavored with chocolate at all. But vanilla cookies are different. ______.\r\n', 'I could eat a horse', 'I’d starve to death', 'It’s none of your business', 'I couldn’t help it', 'I couldn’t help it\r\n', 'I couldn’t help it แปลว่า ช่วยไม่ได้ เพราะ Jim กินคุกกี้ไปจนหมด'),
(9, 12, 'Situation: Sandy is hungry. She wants to eat some cookies she bought last night, but she finds that all the cookies are gone.\r\nSandy: Jim, where are the cookies? Don\'t tell me you ate them all! Again!\r\nJim: Yes, I did. ______. They were so good.\r\nSandy: I thought you didn\'t like cookies.\r\nJim: Well, I don\'t like cookies flavored with chocolate at all. But vanilla cookies are different. ___(?)___.\r\n', 'I love them to death', 'I don’t prefer them', 'They have no flavors at all\r\n', 'I can’t make up my mind', 'I love them to death', 'I love them to death เนื่องจาก Jim บอกว่าไม่ชอบคุกกี้ chocolate แต่สำหรับ vanilla นั้นรักเท่าชีวิต'),
(9, 13, 'Situation: Peter is talking to his friend, Jeff about the assignment.\r\nPeter: Have you handed in the math assignment yet, Jeff?\r\nJeff: No, not yet. Oh, I’m running late. ___(?)____\r\nPeter: ______', 'I must stop talking to you now.', 'Stop saying anything.\r\n.', 'Don’t talk to me now, will you?', 'I’ve got to go to a lecture.\r\n', 'I’ve got to go to a lecture.', 'ประโยคก่อนหน้า Jeff บอกว่าเขากำลังจะสาย แสดงว่าเขาต้องเข้า Lecture'),
(9, 14, 'Situation: Peter is talking to his friend, Jeff about the assignment.\r\nPeter: Have you handed in the math assignment yet, Jeff?\r\nJeff: No, not yet. Oh, I’m running late. ______\r\nPeter: ___(?)____', 'Sorry to keep you. See you later, then.', 'Is that so? Please go now.\r\n', 'Why not? I’ll talk to you again soon.', 'Don’t worry. I think I had better go to the lecture, too.,\r\n', 'Sorry to keep you. See you later, then.', 'หลังจากที่ Peter รู้ว่า Jeff กำลังไปสาย เขาจึงขอโทษ'),
(9, 15, '"Situation: Nell is on the train.\r\nMan: ___(?)___\r\nNell: ______ … Oh no, I’m sorry."\r\n', 'Move to another seat. This is mine.', 'Whose seat are you in now?', 'How come you’re sitting in the wrong seat!', 'Excuse me, I think you’ve taken my seat.\r\n', 'Excuse me, I think you’ve taken my seat.\r\n', 'การพูดกับคนที่ไม่รู้จักหรือคนแปลกหน้าควรใช้คำว่า Excuse me'),
(9, 16, '"Situation: Nell is on the train.\r\nMan: ______\r\nNell: ___(?)___ … Oh no, I’m sorry."\r\n', 'No, it’s my seat. Please find another one.', 'Are you sure you are all right?\r\n', 'I don’t think so, but let me check my ticket.', 'I’m sure you’re wrong. Please take the other one.', 'I don’t think so, but let me check my ticket.\r\n', 'เป็นคำตอบที่เหมาะสมที่สุดในการสนทนากับคนแปลกหน้า'),
